WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.469 --> 00:00:01.935
<i>Previously. on "Bitten"...</i>

2
00:00:01.937 --> 00:00:04.358
A long time ago. maybe 20 years.
a family lived here.

3
00:00:04.359 --> 00:00:07.150
You're always going to
be my little man. Clay.

4
00:00:07.151 --> 00:00:08.850
Elle got killed by a wolf.

5
00:00:08.852 --> 00:00:11.153
I tore her into bits.

6
00:00:12.456 --> 00:00:14.756
Rodrigo is here to see the
repercussions of treachery.

7
00:00:16.493 --> 00:00:18.460
Something came at me in Rochester.

8
00:00:18.462 --> 00:00:19.761
You need to keep me alive

9
00:00:19.763 --> 00:00:21.163
for what's coming.

10
00:00:21.165 --> 00:00:23.065
Wherever they're taking Malcolm Danvers.

11
00:00:23.067 --> 00:00:24.999
is where we are going.

12
00:00:25.001 --> 00:00:26.902
We're witches.

13
00:00:26.904 --> 00:00:28.369
We're being hunted.

14
00:00:28.371 --> 00:00:30.405
They want the werewolf
that you have downstairs.

15
00:00:30.407 --> 00:00:33.107
We're here for the one true
cursed. Malcolm Danvers.

16
00:00:33.109 --> 00:00:35.009
- And so do we.
- You want Malcolm.

17
00:00:35.011 --> 00:00:36.878
but I can't turn him over.

18
00:00:39.649 --> 00:00:41.649
Something's wrong.

19
00:00:49.458 --> 00:00:50.724
When you're done your homework.

20
00:00:50.726 --> 00:00:52.393
one hour of television. that's it.

21
00:00:52.395 --> 00:00:54.095
What do you care?
You won't even be here.

22
00:00:54.097 --> 00:00:55.396
You're supposed to be grounded.

23
00:00:55.398 --> 00:00:57.098
I'm being nice. One hour. that's it.

24
00:00:57.100 --> 00:00:59.433
You're not the boss. Well.
I am when Ruth is away.

25
00:00:59.435 --> 00:01:00.701
I'm locking the doors.

26
00:01:00.703 --> 00:01:02.503
Not going to run away. Yeah. sure.

27
00:01:02.505 --> 00:01:04.738
I've heard that before.
I'll be back before dinner.

28
00:01:07.776 --> 00:01:08.976
Did you do that?

29
00:01:08.978 --> 00:01:10.243
- No.
- I'm serious. Savannah.

30
00:01:10.245 --> 00:01:11.645
If you did that. you have to tell me.

31
00:01:11.647 --> 00:01:14.281
I did tell you. I didn't do it.

32
00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:22.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

33
00:01:28.596 --> 00:01:30.630
Where did you come from?

34
00:01:30.632 --> 00:01:33.566
No need to be afraid. Savannah.

35
00:01:33.568 --> 00:01:36.202
How do you know my name?

36
00:01:36.204 --> 00:01:38.337
Paige?

37
00:01:38.339 --> 00:01:39.839
Paige!

38
00:01:42.009 --> 00:01:43.810
Wha... what's wrong with her?

39
00:01:43.812 --> 00:01:45.645
She'll be fine.

40
00:01:45.647 --> 00:01:48.947
And yet. <i>she</i> gets to go out
and have a fun afternoon.

41
00:01:48.949 --> 00:01:50.682
What do <i>you</i> get to do?

42
00:01:50.684 --> 00:01:52.584
Huh! Homework.

43
00:01:52.586 --> 00:01:53.852
Who are you?

44
00:01:53.854 --> 00:01:55.654
You can call me Aleister.

45
00:01:55.656 --> 00:01:56.855
Savannah!

46
00:02:09.235 --> 00:02:11.236
I've never heard of you before.

47
00:02:11.238 --> 00:02:14.006
The coven doesn't tell you anything.

48
00:02:14.008 --> 00:02:18.243
They're not your family.
they don't care.

49
00:02:18.245 --> 00:02:19.244
But I do.

50
00:02:19.246 --> 00:02:20.645
And I want you to show them

51
00:02:20.647 --> 00:02:21.879
who you really are.

52
00:02:21.881 --> 00:02:25.216
You are the most powerful witch of all.

53
00:02:25.218 --> 00:02:27.519
I don't even have my powers yet.

54
00:02:27.521 --> 00:02:29.720
But you will. Very soon.

55
00:02:29.722 --> 00:02:31.356
And then you can show them

56
00:02:31.358 --> 00:02:34.092
that they shouldn't have
taken you for granted.

57
00:02:36.962 --> 00:02:39.263
It means coming with me.

58
00:02:39.265 --> 00:02:40.731
Is that okay?

59
00:02:59.484 --> 00:03:00.917
I am the lock.

60
00:03:02.253 --> 00:03:03.920
I am the key.

61
00:03:08.093 --> 00:03:09.793
Savannah... Savannah...

62
00:03:10.996 --> 00:03:12.963
<i>Purga hanc domum!</i>

63
00:03:22.506 --> 00:03:24.074
Savannah!

64
00:03:38.954 --> 00:03:44.191
Sync and corrections for www.addic7ed.com

65
00:03:45.153 --> 00:03:59.258
Bitten 2x03 - Hell's Teeth
(February 21. 2015)

66
00:04:28.466 --> 00:04:30.701
The trail's cold. Malcolm's gone.

67
00:04:30.703 --> 00:04:32.403
Someone must've picked him up.

68
00:04:32.405 --> 00:04:34.639
All the doors in the house were open.

69
00:04:34.641 --> 00:04:37.307
That's not a coincidence
and neither is this.

70
00:04:37.309 --> 00:04:38.676
The witches must've taken Malcolm.

71
00:04:38.678 --> 00:04:40.177
They have no idea
what they've unleashed.

72
00:04:40.179 --> 00:04:41.378
The point is. he's gone.

73
00:04:41.380 --> 00:04:43.014
No. No. he can't be.

74
00:04:43.016 --> 00:04:45.782
We promised the Alpha council
his head on a stake.

75
00:04:45.784 --> 00:04:47.217
I'm going to find him.

76
00:04:48.219 --> 00:04:49.553
I'll go with him.

77
00:04:51.456 --> 00:04:54.158
There's no sense in searching the woods.

78
00:04:54.160 --> 00:04:55.359
Malcolm's gone.

79
00:04:55.361 --> 00:04:58.328
There's no sense in any of this.

80
00:05:06.070 --> 00:05:07.403
What now?

81
00:05:07.405 --> 00:05:08.605
We can't just sit around

82
00:05:08.607 --> 00:05:10.006
and wait for the Alphas to return

83
00:05:10.008 --> 00:05:11.641
to mete out their punishment.

84
00:05:11.643 --> 00:05:13.443
Without Malcolm. we have
no way of protecting you

85
00:05:13.445 --> 00:05:14.678
from losing your seat.

86
00:05:14.680 --> 00:05:17.246
This isn't just about Malcolm anymore.

87
00:05:17.248 --> 00:05:20.283
There's a dead Alpha in our war room.

88
00:05:20.285 --> 00:05:21.951
Killing Rodrigo could be interpreted

89
00:05:21.953 --> 00:05:23.486
as a declaration of war.

90
00:05:23.488 --> 00:05:26.222
The other Alphas on the council
cannot know he was here.

91
00:05:26.224 --> 00:05:27.590
Or that Malcolm escaped.

92
00:05:27.592 --> 00:05:29.425
We'll have to hide the body.

93
00:05:53.782 --> 00:05:55.517
We go get Malcolm.

94
00:05:55.519 --> 00:05:56.918
We know where the witches are.

95
00:05:56.920 --> 00:05:58.120
they left their card. okay?

96
00:05:58.122 --> 00:05:59.454
It's in Jeremy's room.

97
00:06:34.055 --> 00:06:35.722
Show yourselves.

98
00:06:37.459 --> 00:06:38.892
We come in peace.

99
00:06:40.561 --> 00:06:41.895
You come empty-handed.

100
00:06:43.430 --> 00:06:45.565
I've no clue what you're talking about.

101
00:06:45.567 --> 00:06:47.433
Malcolm Danvers. I want him back.

102
00:06:47.435 --> 00:06:48.902
Well. you're not getting him.

103
00:06:50.271 --> 00:06:52.105
Then you're not getting this ring.

104
00:06:52.107 --> 00:06:55.308
Which I assume is important to
you since you came back for it.

105
00:07:08.156 --> 00:07:10.657
Stop this right now!

106
00:07:21.602 --> 00:07:22.902
Paige. release him.

107
00:07:22.904 --> 00:07:24.770
I'm only fighting fire with fire.

108
00:07:37.851 --> 00:07:38.983
Jeremy!

109
00:07:46.625 --> 00:07:48.526
My apologies for such rude treatment.

110
00:07:48.528 --> 00:07:50.061
If you ever do anything like that again.

111
00:07:50.063 --> 00:07:51.763
I'll tear your throat out.

112
00:07:51.765 --> 00:07:52.964
Look...

113
00:07:52.966 --> 00:07:54.532
Female werewolf.

114
00:07:54.534 --> 00:07:55.800
We'd heard of your existence.

115
00:07:55.802 --> 00:07:57.668
but to actually see one...

116
00:07:57.670 --> 00:07:59.804
She seems just as barbaric
as the rest of them.

117
00:07:59.806 --> 00:08:01.740
Sorry. was it "witch" or "bitch"?

118
00:08:01.742 --> 00:08:03.006
What have you done with Malcolm?

119
00:08:03.008 --> 00:08:04.408
We asked for your Pack's help.

120
00:08:04.410 --> 00:08:05.676
You wouldn't give it.

121
00:08:05.678 --> 00:08:06.877
So we did what any decent witch would do.

122
00:08:06.879 --> 00:08:08.512
We went and we helped ourselves.

123
00:08:08.514 --> 00:08:09.914
Without understanding the importance

124
00:08:09.915 --> 00:08:11.148
of the person you took.

125
00:08:11.150 --> 00:08:12.550
Oh. we understand all too well.

126
00:08:12.552 --> 00:08:13.751
He's going to be the thing

127
00:08:13.753 --> 00:08:16.721
that saves our girl Savannah.

128
00:08:16.723 --> 00:08:18.055
We should be on our way.

129
00:08:21.226 --> 00:08:23.026
Uh-uh. you stay in our eye-line.

130
00:08:24.729 --> 00:08:26.130
They have Malcolm.

131
00:08:26.132 --> 00:08:27.330
- Let's go get him!
- Nick...

132
00:08:27.332 --> 00:08:28.732
We need him.

133
00:08:28.734 --> 00:08:30.734
We need him to lure this demon

134
00:08:30.736 --> 00:08:32.736
who calls himself Aleister Vi.

135
00:08:32.738 --> 00:08:34.071
How do you know he wants Malcolm?

136
00:08:35.573 --> 00:08:37.741
We can communicate with Savannah.

137
00:08:37.743 --> 00:08:39.576
That's how we know about Aleister.

138
00:08:39.578 --> 00:08:41.578
And that there is a
werewolf on the compound

139
00:08:41.580 --> 00:08:43.280
that gave up Malcolm's name.

140
00:08:43.282 --> 00:08:45.715
They attacked his house in
Rochester. but he escaped.

141
00:08:45.717 --> 00:08:47.417
But as dangerous as your wolf may be.

142
00:08:47.419 --> 00:08:49.886
he pales in comparison to Aleister.

143
00:08:49.888 --> 00:08:53.256
Savannah has been through so much.

144
00:08:53.258 --> 00:08:54.857
She's impressionable.

145
00:08:56.426 --> 00:08:58.895
This monster...

146
00:08:58.897 --> 00:09:02.564
abducted her right from our home.

147
00:09:04.101 --> 00:09:05.835
A 12-year-old girl.

148
00:09:07.604 --> 00:09:09.772
We'll help you find your little girl.

149
00:09:09.774 --> 00:09:11.907
Then we want Malcolm back.

150
00:09:11.909 --> 00:09:13.609
Oh. <i>now</i> you want to play.

151
00:09:13.611 --> 00:09:15.778
I don't want to play.
I just want Malcolm.

152
00:09:15.780 --> 00:09:18.614
And this seems to be the only
way I'm going to get him.

153
00:09:18.616 --> 00:09:20.549
Now. if Aleister shows
up with the followers.

154
00:09:20.551 --> 00:09:22.618
you're going to need our assistance.

155
00:09:22.620 --> 00:09:24.453
They're brutal fighters.

156
00:09:24.455 --> 00:09:25.787
We've seen the evidence.

157
00:09:31.127 --> 00:09:32.928
Our plan is to entice him.

158
00:09:32.930 --> 00:09:34.796
We'll use Malcolm as the lure.

159
00:09:34.798 --> 00:09:36.264
Once we contain Aleister.

160
00:09:36.266 --> 00:09:38.934
then we will force him
to take us to our girl.

161
00:09:38.936 --> 00:09:40.836
- And we get Malcolm.
- As you wish.

162
00:09:40.838 --> 00:09:42.670
We'll have no further use for him.

163
00:09:43.639 --> 00:09:45.807
You two go with him now.

164
00:09:45.809 --> 00:09:49.109
The rest of us will follow shortly.

165
00:09:49.111 --> 00:09:52.146
I'm so glad you decided
to be on our side.

166
00:09:52.148 --> 00:09:53.648
There are no sides.

167
00:09:53.650 --> 00:09:57.017
We're all just trying
to get what we want.

168
00:09:57.019 --> 00:09:58.152
Let's go. Paige.

169
00:10:00.956 --> 00:10:02.456
So what do you. like. have Malcolm

170
00:10:02.458 --> 00:10:04.124
- in your trunk or something?
- Nice try.

171
00:10:04.126 --> 00:10:05.525
We're not letting you anywhere near him

172
00:10:05.527 --> 00:10:07.161
until the deed is done.

173
00:10:07.163 --> 00:10:10.497
Don't worry. We're
taking good care of him.

174
00:10:23.177 --> 00:10:24.378
How responsible.

175
00:10:24.380 --> 00:10:25.979
Most people wouldn't pull over.

176
00:10:25.981 --> 00:10:29.483
Most people wouldn't
pick up hitchhikers.

177
00:10:29.485 --> 00:10:31.617
I'll be just a sec. We'll
get back on the road.

178
00:10:31.619 --> 00:10:32.818
I've always been perplexed

179
00:10:32.820 --> 00:10:34.687
by the fear of hitchhikers.

180
00:10:34.689 --> 00:10:37.690
Sometimes it's nice to have
some company on the road.

181
00:10:37.692 --> 00:10:38.958
Sometimes it's nice

182
00:10:38.960 --> 00:10:41.361
to have a small. meaningful exchange

183
00:10:41.363 --> 00:10:42.862
before you part ways.

184
00:10:47.702 --> 00:10:48.967
<i>Protege me!</i>

185
00:10:48.969 --> 00:10:51.771
<i>Constringe eum.</i>

186
00:10:54.408 --> 00:10:55.608
What is this?

187
00:10:55.610 --> 00:10:57.610
A small. meaningful exchange.

188
00:10:59.012 --> 00:11:01.246
How do we know we're not
walking into another massacre

189
00:11:01.248 --> 00:11:02.581
like Rochester?

190
00:11:02.583 --> 00:11:03.916
We'll have the tactical advantage.

191
00:11:03.918 --> 00:11:05.583
He'll be walking into whatever trap

192
00:11:05.585 --> 00:11:07.185
the witches set for him. Are
you sure we can trust them?

193
00:11:07.187 --> 00:11:09.721
If we want Malcolm. we have no choice.

194
00:11:12.226 --> 00:11:13.558
We have guests.

195
00:11:19.698 --> 00:11:21.098
Can I help you?

196
00:11:21.100 --> 00:11:23.100
Jeremy Danvers.

197
00:11:23.102 --> 00:11:25.403
Eduardo Escobado.

198
00:11:25.405 --> 00:11:26.738
I'm from the Spanish Pack

199
00:11:26.740 --> 00:11:28.940
and I'm here to find my Alpha.

200
00:11:36.664 --> 00:11:37.865
Rodrigo Sanchez was here

201
00:11:37.867 --> 00:11:39.967
a few days ago for the council meeting.

202
00:11:39.969 --> 00:11:42.002
If he told you that he was
coming here yesterday.

203
00:11:42.004 --> 00:11:43.937
then he didn't make it. Or he lied.

204
00:11:43.939 --> 00:11:46.540
I think <i>someone</i> lied.

205
00:11:46.542 --> 00:11:47.674
Maybe him.

206
00:11:49.010 --> 00:11:50.210
Maybe you.

207
00:11:50.212 --> 00:11:51.612
Oh. you might want to rephrase that.

208
00:11:51.614 --> 00:11:53.213
Clay...

209
00:11:53.215 --> 00:11:55.248
Our friends are just
concerned about their Alpha.

210
00:11:55.250 --> 00:11:57.017
In their position. who wouldn't be?

211
00:11:57.019 --> 00:12:00.020
My position is that this is the
last place Rodrigo had been

212
00:12:00.022 --> 00:12:01.721
before he went off the radar.

213
00:12:01.723 --> 00:12:04.257
I want to find him.

214
00:12:08.496 --> 00:12:10.030
Would you give us a minute. please.

215
00:12:10.032 --> 00:12:11.364
Of course.

216
00:12:18.505 --> 00:12:20.372
I understand that you're worried.

217
00:12:20.374 --> 00:12:23.509
Your Alpha missing. so far from home.

218
00:12:23.511 --> 00:12:25.878
I suggest you look in
your own ranks first.

219
00:12:25.880 --> 00:12:28.213
<i>Our</i> ranks? This is the house

220
00:12:28.215 --> 00:12:30.382
that has seen much death recently.

221
00:12:30.384 --> 00:12:32.217
I think that might include my Alpha.

222
00:12:32.219 --> 00:12:33.718
Do you have the nerve to say that

223
00:12:33.720 --> 00:12:35.687
in front of the council?

224
00:12:35.689 --> 00:12:38.390
They'll all be here within a few days.

225
00:12:38.392 --> 00:12:41.326
You know how we feel
about false accusations.

226
00:12:44.064 --> 00:12:45.830
- Need a hand?
- No. I got it.

227
00:12:58.511 --> 00:13:02.047
Every Pack has skeletons in the closet.

228
00:13:02.049 --> 00:13:03.782
You have your father.

229
00:13:03.784 --> 00:13:05.649
And... where is he?

230
00:13:05.651 --> 00:13:07.818
- This conversation is over.
- Fine.

231
00:13:07.820 --> 00:13:09.820
You want me to leave?

232
00:13:09.822 --> 00:13:12.256
Show me your house.

233
00:13:12.258 --> 00:13:14.358
- All of it.
- Eduardo...

234
00:13:16.395 --> 00:13:19.597
I don't have to show you anything.

235
00:13:19.599 --> 00:13:21.431
Then humor me.

236
00:13:21.433 --> 00:13:24.134
Please.

237
00:13:24.136 --> 00:13:27.004
I need to go back to
them with something.

238
00:13:27.006 --> 00:13:28.806
Be my guest.

239
00:13:28.808 --> 00:13:31.241
The scent of death
still lingers here.

240
00:13:31.243 --> 00:13:33.944
Two Mutts were killed in
the attack on Stonehaven.

241
00:13:33.946 --> 00:13:36.981
Elena was almost killed
protecting our Pack

242
00:13:36.983 --> 00:13:38.748
and everything down here.

243
00:13:38.750 --> 00:13:41.451
There is also the stench of bleach.

244
00:13:41.453 --> 00:13:43.920
as if you're trying
to cover something up.

245
00:13:43.922 --> 00:13:46.189
There was a lot of carnage.

246
00:13:46.191 --> 00:13:48.791
We take pride in our home

247
00:13:48.793 --> 00:13:51.027
and everything in it.

248
00:13:51.029 --> 00:13:52.762
Have you seen our Legacy?

249
00:13:54.331 --> 00:13:56.432
Quite the collection. yes.

250
00:13:56.434 --> 00:13:59.669
I may have leapt to a hasty assumption.

251
00:14:01.071 --> 00:14:03.039
I've seen everything I need to see.

252
00:14:03.041 --> 00:14:05.708
My humble apologies.

253
00:14:05.710 --> 00:14:07.476
One can only hope that every Pack member

254
00:14:07.478 --> 00:14:08.978
is as loyal to their Alpha

255
00:14:08.980 --> 00:14:11.880
as you clearly are to Rodrigo.

256
00:14:11.882 --> 00:14:14.450
I wish you best efforts in finding him.

257
00:14:14.452 --> 00:14:17.253
If we hear anything. we'll
be sure to contact you.

258
00:14:19.055 --> 00:14:20.589
Let's finish this.

259
00:14:26.095 --> 00:14:28.797
We could just burn Rodrigo here.

260
00:14:28.799 --> 00:14:32.400
We should be burning him
and Malcolm at the same time.

261
00:14:32.402 --> 00:14:35.236
We should've killed Malcolm
when we had a chance.

262
00:14:35.238 --> 00:14:38.006
We dispose of Rodrigo
now. the right way.

263
00:14:38.008 --> 00:14:40.341
This <i>can't</i> come back on Jeremy.

264
00:14:45.748 --> 00:14:47.248
He gave me a bit of trouble.

265
00:14:47.250 --> 00:14:49.116
but I got him right where I want him.

266
00:14:50.219 --> 00:14:51.819
Okay. We'll wait here

267
00:14:51.821 --> 00:14:53.921
until you send word you're ready for us.

268
00:14:53.923 --> 00:14:56.558
Relax. Malcolm. you're
going to hurt yourself.

269
00:14:56.560 --> 00:14:57.925
The restraining spell I've got on you

270
00:14:57.927 --> 00:14:59.694
is going to make the
cage you just escaped

271
00:14:59.696 --> 00:15:01.428
seem like a Kleenex box.
Are you the creature

272
00:15:01.430 --> 00:15:03.698
- that attacked me in Rochester?
- No.

273
00:15:03.700 --> 00:15:05.432
But we are going to give you to him.

274
00:15:05.434 --> 00:15:08.102
You're just a goat on a chain.

275
00:15:08.104 --> 00:15:09.837
And if we need to defend ourselves.

276
00:15:09.839 --> 00:15:12.740
trust me. we've got that covered.

277
00:15:12.742 --> 00:15:16.776
So. this is what a great
werewolf looks like.

278
00:15:18.846 --> 00:15:20.380
Quite the specimen.

279
00:15:20.382 --> 00:15:22.416
I can see why he wants you.

280
00:15:22.418 --> 00:15:24.751
We can work together here. you know.

281
00:15:24.753 --> 00:15:26.286
eliminate him.

282
00:15:26.288 --> 00:15:28.021
Train you to work with us?

283
00:15:28.023 --> 00:15:29.789
Oh. I don't think so.

284
00:15:29.791 --> 00:15:32.226
I've seen what he's capable of.

285
00:15:32.228 --> 00:15:33.760
You need me.

286
00:15:33.762 --> 00:15:35.228
Of course we do.

287
00:15:35.230 --> 00:15:36.830
As the bait.

288
00:15:41.769 --> 00:15:44.237
He is the one true path.

289
00:15:44.239 --> 00:15:46.840
He's the one true light on the path.

290
00:15:46.842 --> 00:15:48.908
The key to our gate.

291
00:15:48.910 --> 00:15:52.177
The light we follow through the gate.

292
00:15:52.179 --> 00:15:55.948
The key that unlocks us into the great...

293
00:15:55.950 --> 00:15:57.149
Hello?

294
00:15:57.151 --> 00:15:58.584
...The light we follow.

295
00:15:58.586 --> 00:16:00.653
The truth we follow...

296
00:16:02.188 --> 00:16:05.658
Don't let her bother you.
She's not feeling well.

297
00:16:05.660 --> 00:16:07.960
Was she the woman that was
screaming the other night?

298
00:16:07.962 --> 00:16:10.162
No. that was the woman from Rochester.

299
00:16:10.164 --> 00:16:11.930
Some pains to do with her pregnancy.

300
00:16:11.932 --> 00:16:13.431
But she's fine now.

301
00:16:13.433 --> 00:16:15.300
How is the new furniture in your room?

302
00:16:15.302 --> 00:16:17.102
Is everything to your liking?

303
00:16:17.104 --> 00:16:18.570
No.

304
00:16:18.572 --> 00:16:21.640
I'm locked away here.
Like I was with Ruth

305
00:16:21.642 --> 00:16:23.040
and Paige.

306
00:16:23.042 --> 00:16:26.177
It's for your safety.
We've been over that.

307
00:16:26.179 --> 00:16:28.346
And what power would you
like to learn today?

308
00:16:28.348 --> 00:16:30.047
Anything you want. Think of something

309
00:16:30.049 --> 00:16:32.517
your coven would never teach you.

310
00:16:32.519 --> 00:16:35.219
Maybe you could tell me something.

311
00:16:35.221 --> 00:16:37.889
I had a strange dream last night.

312
00:16:37.891 --> 00:16:39.323
A dream?

313
00:16:39.325 --> 00:16:41.492
Tell me about it.

314
00:16:41.494 --> 00:16:43.094
There was a man in a barn.

315
00:16:43.096 --> 00:16:46.297
I think that's where
he's hiding. only...

316
00:16:46.299 --> 00:16:48.699
he turns into a wolf.

317
00:16:48.701 --> 00:16:50.334
A wolf?

318
00:16:50.336 --> 00:16:51.535
A werewolf.

319
00:16:51.537 --> 00:16:54.071
And he's very powerful.

320
00:16:54.073 --> 00:16:55.606
I think his name was...

321
00:16:55.608 --> 00:16:58.642
Martin or... Marshall...

322
00:16:58.644 --> 00:17:01.044
Malcolm?

323
00:17:01.046 --> 00:17:02.379
That's it.

324
00:17:02.381 --> 00:17:04.648
And when you appeared. you were happy.

325
00:17:04.650 --> 00:17:06.517
You said that you'd
been looking for him.

326
00:17:08.386 --> 00:17:10.788
Your vision was very useful.

327
00:17:10.790 --> 00:17:13.190
If only we knew where this barn was.

328
00:17:13.192 --> 00:17:15.591
There was a sign. I wrote it down.

329
00:17:21.999 --> 00:17:23.666
Hm.

330
00:17:23.668 --> 00:17:25.468
Thank you for this. Savannah.

331
00:17:26.603 --> 00:17:28.871
Is there something else
you want to tell me?

332
00:17:31.074 --> 00:17:32.608
No.

333
00:17:35.446 --> 00:17:37.447
I am the lock.

334
00:17:37.449 --> 00:17:39.315
And I'm the key.

335
00:17:42.453 --> 00:17:43.953
Don't go alone.

336
00:17:43.955 --> 00:17:44.954
Why not?

337
00:17:44.956 --> 00:17:48.123
The wolf isn't by himself.

338
00:17:48.125 --> 00:17:50.425
That's fine.

339
00:17:53.563 --> 00:17:55.731
We'll pick this up again later.

340
00:18:31.400 --> 00:18:33.534
Hey.

341
00:18:33.536 --> 00:18:34.735
Talk to me.

342
00:18:34.737 --> 00:18:37.337
Clay. look. I know you.

343
00:18:37.339 --> 00:18:38.873
And I know being in Baton Rouge

344
00:18:38.875 --> 00:18:40.441
stirred something up.

345
00:18:43.545 --> 00:18:46.179
My parents didn't abandon me.

346
00:18:46.181 --> 00:18:47.748
None of that's true.

347
00:18:47.750 --> 00:18:50.851
Malcolm killed my mother.

348
00:18:50.853 --> 00:18:52.786
slaughtered her.

349
00:18:52.788 --> 00:18:56.489
My father. he came home.

350
00:18:56.491 --> 00:18:58.558
saw it...

351
00:18:58.560 --> 00:19:01.094
He took his own life.

352
00:19:01.096 --> 00:19:03.931
But after all these years... I was wrong.

353
00:19:07.968 --> 00:19:10.269
Malcolm taught me to fight.

354
00:19:10.271 --> 00:19:11.604
to kill.

355
00:19:11.606 --> 00:19:14.407
I should've used that against him.

356
00:19:14.409 --> 00:19:16.910
We had him. Elena.

357
00:19:16.912 --> 00:19:19.612
We had him. I could've
ripped his throat out.

358
00:19:24.183 --> 00:19:25.784
When this thing with
the witches is over.

359
00:19:25.786 --> 00:19:27.719
we make him pay for what he's done.

360
00:19:40.033 --> 00:19:42.400
This alliance thing...

361
00:19:42.402 --> 00:19:43.836
What are we getting ourselves into?

362
00:19:43.838 --> 00:19:45.671
They painted us into a corner.

363
00:19:45.673 --> 00:19:46.905
Once their witch shows up with Malcolm.

364
00:19:46.907 --> 00:19:48.774
they get us everything.

365
00:19:53.379 --> 00:19:54.746
I have a bad feeling about this.

366
00:19:54.748 --> 00:19:56.448
I don't want to hear it.

367
00:19:56.450 --> 00:19:58.516
Fine...

368
00:19:58.518 --> 00:20:01.819
Do you want me to admit that I'm scared?

369
00:20:01.821 --> 00:20:02.820
I am scared.

370
00:20:02.822 --> 00:20:04.956
Paige. we are doing this.

371
00:20:04.958 --> 00:20:06.157
We stand down now.

372
00:20:06.159 --> 00:20:07.925
Savannah may never come back.

373
00:20:07.927 --> 00:20:10.561
I want her back just as much as you do.

374
00:20:10.563 --> 00:20:13.764
I was there when he took her.

375
00:20:13.766 --> 00:20:15.833
<i>I</i> didn't protect her.

376
00:20:17.469 --> 00:20:20.204
This thing. this Aleister...

377
00:20:20.206 --> 00:20:22.072
I will not let our future

378
00:20:22.074 --> 00:20:23.340
be dictated this man.

379
00:20:23.342 --> 00:20:24.842
He's not just a man.

380
00:20:24.844 --> 00:20:27.712
Paige. this is all we have.

381
00:21:00.077 --> 00:21:01.578
Savannah...

382
00:21:04.381 --> 00:21:05.981
are you with us?

383
00:21:12.423 --> 00:21:14.557
<i>I'm with you.</i>

384
00:21:14.559 --> 00:21:16.492
Savannah.

385
00:21:16.494 --> 00:21:18.294
Are you okay?

386
00:21:18.296 --> 00:21:20.596
<i>I'm fine.</i>

387
00:21:20.598 --> 00:21:22.531
<i>I gave him the information.</i>

388
00:21:22.533 --> 00:21:24.033
<i>just like you wanted.</i>

389
00:21:24.035 --> 00:21:26.401
<i>- He was happy.</i>
- You didn't tell him

390
00:21:26.403 --> 00:21:28.537
that we can communicate like this?

391
00:21:28.539 --> 00:21:30.272
<i>No.</i>

392
00:21:30.274 --> 00:21:31.473
<i>I said I had a vision.</i>

393
00:21:31.475 --> 00:21:33.108
<i>just like you told me to.</i>

394
00:21:34.678 --> 00:21:36.811
Is he coming to the farm?

395
00:21:40.783 --> 00:21:42.884
<i>I think so...</i> It's like a...

396
00:21:42.886 --> 00:21:45.554
witchy Skype call or...

397
00:21:45.556 --> 00:21:46.988
witch Facetime...

398
00:21:46.990 --> 00:21:48.123
Would you listen?

399
00:21:51.060 --> 00:21:54.729
Savannah. we will
bring you home today.

400
00:21:56.599 --> 00:21:59.901
It's quiet here now.

401
00:21:59.903 --> 00:22:02.103
<i>The woman from Rochester.</i>

402
00:22:02.105 --> 00:22:04.171
<i>the one who he told you was screaming...</i>

403
00:22:04.173 --> 00:22:05.773
Woman from Rochester?
Whoa. whoa. easy. easy!

404
00:22:05.775 --> 00:22:06.975
Let them do their thing.

405
00:22:06.977 --> 00:22:10.877
<i>Nobody was hurting her.</i>

406
00:22:10.879 --> 00:22:12.713
<i>He said that she was in pain</i>

407
00:22:12.715 --> 00:22:13.914
<i>because of the baby.</i>

408
00:22:13.916 --> 00:22:15.649
- That's Rachel.
- Logan. don't...

409
00:22:15.651 --> 00:22:16.850
- Logan!
- She said something

410
00:22:16.852 --> 00:22:18.119
about a pregnant woman.

411
00:22:18.121 --> 00:22:19.886
Ask her about that. What about the baby?

412
00:22:19.888 --> 00:22:22.089
- Ask her where she is!
- Damn it. get him off her!

413
00:22:23.559 --> 00:22:26.026
Paige. Paige. Paige!

414
00:22:26.028 --> 00:22:28.128
Paige. come back to us. Paige!

415
00:22:28.130 --> 00:22:30.062
Paige! Paige!

416
00:22:33.649 --> 00:22:34.916
Paige? It's all right.

417
00:22:34.918 --> 00:22:36.918
Come back! Come back.

418
00:22:36.920 --> 00:22:39.888
Come back. it's okay.
Paige. Come back...

419
00:22:39.890 --> 00:22:41.422
What happened? Is she okay?

420
00:22:41.424 --> 00:22:43.424
You break a channel like that.
you risk terrible damage.

421
00:22:43.426 --> 00:22:44.858
The woman that Savannah described.

422
00:22:44.860 --> 00:22:46.827
it's... it's his girlfriend.

423
00:22:46.829 --> 00:22:48.129
She's pregnant?

424
00:22:48.131 --> 00:22:50.331
Yeah. just a couple of months.

425
00:22:50.333 --> 00:22:51.698
Malcolm had her in Rochester.

426
00:22:51.700 --> 00:22:53.267
Aleister must have found her there

427
00:22:53.269 --> 00:22:54.468
and brought her to his compound.

428
00:22:58.172 --> 00:22:59.973
Paige! Are you okay?

429
00:23:01.476 --> 00:23:03.444
Yeah. it's kind of like a...

430
00:23:03.446 --> 00:23:05.612
a gin hangover.

431
00:23:05.614 --> 00:23:08.281
Or worse: Schnapps.

432
00:23:08.283 --> 00:23:09.616
Ughh...

433
00:23:09.618 --> 00:23:11.151
All right. where is she?
How do we find her?

434
00:23:11.153 --> 00:23:12.886
Look. just because
he has your girlfriend

435
00:23:12.888 --> 00:23:14.520
doesn't mean we alter the plan.

436
00:23:14.522 --> 00:23:16.156
He has Savannah as well.

437
00:23:16.158 --> 00:23:18.224
We all want to find out where they are.

438
00:23:19.493 --> 00:23:20.693
She's alive.

439
00:23:20.695 --> 00:23:22.562
- Yes.
- I knew it.

440
00:23:45.719 --> 00:23:48.387
For your mother.

441
00:23:48.389 --> 00:23:49.721
For Philip...

442
00:23:49.723 --> 00:23:51.656
Pete. Antonio...

443
00:23:51.658 --> 00:23:54.126
Malcolm dies today.

444
00:23:55.795 --> 00:23:57.129
Let's go.

445
00:24:00.867 --> 00:24:03.869
You're planning on putting
Malcolm in there?

446
00:24:03.871 --> 00:24:06.705
Bridget should be able to
hold him with a spell.

447
00:24:06.707 --> 00:24:08.239
And when Aleister goes in after him.

448
00:24:08.241 --> 00:24:10.408
that's when we'll make our move.

449
00:24:10.410 --> 00:24:12.978
We'd better put him right here.

450
00:24:12.980 --> 00:24:14.746
There's more places
for us to lie in wait.

451
00:24:14.748 --> 00:24:17.682
then we can surround them.

452
00:24:17.684 --> 00:24:20.985
All right. That's what we'll do.

453
00:24:20.987 --> 00:24:23.087
We should be able to contain him.

454
00:24:23.089 --> 00:24:25.256
And then we will force him to tell us

455
00:24:25.258 --> 00:24:26.590
where his compound is.

456
00:24:26.592 --> 00:24:28.159
With spells?

457
00:24:29.561 --> 00:24:32.030
By whatever means necessary.

458
00:24:32.032 --> 00:24:33.764
We don't like to harm.

459
00:24:33.766 --> 00:24:36.134
We don't like to torture.

460
00:24:36.136 --> 00:24:39.069
We also don't like having
our girls kidnapped.

461
00:24:44.108 --> 00:24:46.577
Two ways in; that's not ideal.

462
00:24:46.579 --> 00:24:47.778
Means there's two ways out.

463
00:24:47.780 --> 00:24:49.346
We'll be ready for them.

464
00:24:52.617 --> 00:24:55.352
It'll tell us when he's nearby.

465
00:24:55.354 --> 00:24:58.555
Clay mentioned that Aleister's
followers are immune to pain.

466
00:24:58.557 --> 00:25:00.857
Is that some sort of spell?

467
00:25:00.859 --> 00:25:03.026
Not one that I've ever seen.

468
00:25:07.098 --> 00:25:08.498
You and I will take a position

469
00:25:08.500 --> 00:25:10.166
up on that hill with Nick.

470
00:25:10.168 --> 00:25:11.734
We'll move to surround
Aleister when he arrives

471
00:25:11.736 --> 00:25:13.302
and deal with any followers
that come with him.

472
00:25:13.304 --> 00:25:14.904
Okay. sounds good.

473
00:25:16.006 --> 00:25:17.974
I'm glad she's alive. Logan.

474
00:25:17.976 --> 00:25:19.175
First thing we do is we make sure

475
00:25:19.177 --> 00:25:20.910
that Aleister does not get away.

476
00:25:20.912 --> 00:25:22.845
We deal with Malcolm

477
00:25:22.847 --> 00:25:24.814
and then we're going to find Rachel.

478
00:25:24.816 --> 00:25:26.848
We are going to bring her home.

479
00:25:27.817 --> 00:25:29.351
Okay.

480
00:26:02.418 --> 00:26:03.951
Whatever you think of me.

481
00:26:03.953 --> 00:26:06.287
whatever I've done to you.

482
00:26:06.289 --> 00:26:07.888
let it go

483
00:26:07.890 --> 00:26:10.024
and we'll survive this together.

484
00:26:10.026 --> 00:26:11.659
But don't let this happen.

485
00:26:11.661 --> 00:26:13.027
I prefer you kill me

486
00:26:13.029 --> 00:26:15.029
than let me be taken
by whatever's coming.

487
00:26:15.031 --> 00:26:17.665
You're worth more to all
of us alive than dead.

488
00:26:20.235 --> 00:26:21.368
For now.

489
00:27:06.112 --> 00:27:09.215
It's been a couple of hours.

490
00:27:09.217 --> 00:27:12.485
We're going to wait
as long as we have to.

491
00:27:12.487 --> 00:27:13.819
Be patient.

492
00:27:15.021 --> 00:27:17.122
We all need this to work.

493
00:27:40.279 --> 00:27:41.913
Ah!

494
00:28:11.543 --> 00:28:12.976
He's coming.

495
00:28:39.804 --> 00:28:41.471
Hello. Malcolm.

496
00:28:42.940 --> 00:28:45.408
I have been looking for you.

497
00:29:01.039 --> 00:29:02.239
Tell me.

498
00:29:02.241 --> 00:29:04.874
are you the most powerful werewolf?

499
00:29:07.645 --> 00:29:11.148
Whatever happens. we stay on Malcolm.

500
00:29:11.150 --> 00:29:13.583
He's not getting out of here alive.

501
00:29:22.593 --> 00:29:25.962
Oh. I guess you can't speak.

502
00:29:25.964 --> 00:29:27.229
Don't worry about that.

503
00:29:27.231 --> 00:29:30.299
We will have plenty of time to talk.

504
00:29:30.301 --> 00:29:31.768
We want Savannah.

505
00:29:31.770 --> 00:29:34.570
They aren't done filling
her with their poison.

506
00:29:34.572 --> 00:29:36.238
I promise you that if you hurt her.

507
00:29:36.240 --> 00:29:37.473
you will suffer.

508
00:29:37.475 --> 00:29:39.708
Do you hear that?

509
00:29:42.812 --> 00:29:44.413
Suffering.

510
00:29:44.415 --> 00:29:47.483
I can teach them all about it.

511
00:29:48.418 --> 00:29:50.719
I'm looking forward to it.

512
00:29:50.721 --> 00:29:52.153
Who are you?

513
00:29:52.155 --> 00:29:54.756
Now... I wonder.

514
00:29:54.758 --> 00:29:58.193
which one of them is holding you.

515
00:29:58.195 --> 00:30:00.395
She needs to die first.

516
00:30:14.343 --> 00:30:15.676
Bridget!

517
00:30:17.546 --> 00:30:19.214
Bridget! Bridget!

518
00:30:19.216 --> 00:30:20.615
Oh...

519
00:31:35.890 --> 00:31:37.322
Go get Malcolm!

520
00:31:53.540 --> 00:31:55.273
We need to get her out of here!

521
00:31:55.275 --> 00:31:56.575
- Go inside!
- Okay.

522
00:32:12.324 --> 00:32:14.726
No. I don't suppose I'll be
able to break this circle

523
00:32:14.728 --> 00:32:17.961
- no matter how many times I try.
- Who are you?

524
00:32:17.963 --> 00:32:19.730
Oh. in time you will know me.

525
00:32:19.732 --> 00:32:21.999
We've never done anything to you.

526
00:32:22.001 --> 00:32:24.034
Yes. you have. Ruth.

527
00:32:24.036 --> 00:32:26.537
More than you know right now.

528
00:32:26.539 --> 00:32:29.106
That's okay. I'm going to make sure

529
00:32:29.108 --> 00:32:31.475
that it sinks in.

530
00:32:31.477 --> 00:32:34.044
I'm afraid you won't
see your girl again.

531
00:32:34.046 --> 00:32:37.914
But thank you for bringing
me the wolf I need.

532
00:32:37.916 --> 00:32:39.883
I'm going to go collect him now.

533
00:32:52.863 --> 00:32:54.264
You'll be okay.

534
00:32:54.266 --> 00:32:55.598
We'll fix you up fast.

535
00:32:57.301 --> 00:32:58.501
Too late.

536
00:32:58.503 --> 00:33:01.237
Don't give up. Bridget. please!

537
00:33:12.415 --> 00:33:13.816
Nick!

538
00:33:41.911 --> 00:33:43.477
Oh. come on!

539
00:34:02.431 --> 00:34:03.764
<i>Quiesce.</i>

540
00:34:09.003 --> 00:34:11.138
You couldn't have done
that two minutes ago?

541
00:34:20.215 --> 00:34:21.548
She's gone.

542
00:34:35.897 --> 00:34:37.330
Clay!

543
00:34:39.401 --> 00:34:40.600
All right!

544
00:34:57.417 --> 00:34:59.185
You want to end this now?

545
00:34:59.187 --> 00:35:00.419
Yes.

546
00:35:00.421 --> 00:35:02.488
Then you'll die.

547
00:35:02.490 --> 00:35:03.855
I had such high hopes for you.

548
00:35:03.857 --> 00:35:05.924
I'm not going to enjoy this.

549
00:35:05.926 --> 00:35:07.058
I will.

550
00:35:11.130 --> 00:35:13.399
- Ugh!
- Oof!

551
00:35:57.008 --> 00:35:58.142
Ugh!

552
00:36:03.182 --> 00:36:05.816
You asked for this. you stupid bitch.

553
00:36:05.818 --> 00:36:08.618
Time to say goodbye.

554
00:36:21.166 --> 00:36:22.298
Ugh!

555
00:36:38.349 --> 00:36:39.815
Goodbye.

556
00:36:43.086 --> 00:36:44.219
Run.

557
00:36:49.259 --> 00:36:52.928
The other werewolf I had lied to me.

558
00:36:52.930 --> 00:36:55.364
Malcolm wasn't the strongest after all.

559
00:37:32.867 --> 00:37:35.335
- Elena!
- Elena!

560
00:37:35.337 --> 00:37:36.703
Elena!

561
00:37:53.321 --> 00:37:55.354
Elena?

562
00:37:55.356 --> 00:37:58.057
Elena!

563
00:37:58.059 --> 00:38:00.159
Elena!

564
00:38:17.993 --> 00:38:19.560
Rot in hell.

565
00:39:04.481 --> 00:39:05.681
Is there anything I can do?

566
00:39:05.683 --> 00:39:07.250
Please. just leave us alone.

567
00:39:07.252 --> 00:39:09.718
Look. I... I just wanted to
say how sorry I am...

568
00:39:09.720 --> 00:39:11.487
for your loss. it was...

569
00:39:11.489 --> 00:39:12.688
I told Ruth

570
00:39:12.690 --> 00:39:14.023
that this was a mistake.

571
00:39:14.025 --> 00:39:16.892
You... you did everything you could.

572
00:39:16.894 --> 00:39:18.460
You will have your revenge.

573
00:39:18.462 --> 00:39:19.795
Revenge?

574
00:39:21.765 --> 00:39:24.199
We're not brutes like you.

575
00:39:25.835 --> 00:39:29.505
We use our magic only to do
good. to defend ourselves.

576
00:39:29.507 --> 00:39:31.239
Not anymore.

577
00:39:34.143 --> 00:39:36.311
It's just that I thought
that this would be the end.

578
00:39:36.313 --> 00:39:37.512
that Savannah would be home.

579
00:39:37.514 --> 00:39:39.514
that Bridget would be alive.

580
00:39:39.516 --> 00:39:42.150
We will get Savannah.

581
00:39:42.152 --> 00:39:43.751
And Elena and Logan.

582
00:39:43.753 --> 00:39:44.953
and we will make him pay

583
00:39:44.955 --> 00:39:46.654
for what he did to Bridget.

584
00:39:50.091 --> 00:39:51.659
I never had a...

585
00:39:51.661 --> 00:39:55.262
never needed... a sister.

586
00:39:55.264 --> 00:39:57.665
Because I had them...

587
00:39:57.667 --> 00:40:01.636
Bridget and Savannah.

588
00:40:01.638 --> 00:40:03.371
And I took them both for granted.

589
00:40:03.373 --> 00:40:04.705
and now they are both gone.

590
00:40:04.707 --> 00:40:06.073
because of me.

591
00:40:06.075 --> 00:40:08.709
Look. this is not your fault.

592
00:40:08.711 --> 00:40:11.778
That... guy. that thing...

593
00:40:11.780 --> 00:40:14.548
he's the one that did
all of this. not...

594
00:40:14.550 --> 00:40:15.883
not you.

595
00:40:21.088 --> 00:40:24.090
How do you know?

596
00:40:24.092 --> 00:40:25.692
You just met us.

597
00:40:25.694 --> 00:40:29.128
And you don't know anything about me.

598
00:40:29.130 --> 00:40:31.565
You risked your life
to save your friend.

599
00:40:31.567 --> 00:40:34.000
That tells me everything I need to know.

600
00:40:40.040 --> 00:40:42.375
Tell Ruth I'll be in in a minute.

601
00:42:08.092 --> 00:42:11.428
Okay. I need you to focus for me.

602
00:42:11.430 --> 00:42:12.896
Can you do that?

603
00:42:12.898 --> 00:42:16.066
One more time: where did they take her?

604
00:42:16.068 --> 00:42:18.534
Where did they take Elena and Logan?

605
00:42:18.536 --> 00:42:20.603
The key to the gate.

606
00:42:20.605 --> 00:42:23.906
the great undoing... is coming...

607
00:42:23.908 --> 00:42:25.976
Savannah. where did they take her?

608
00:42:25.978 --> 00:42:27.543
Is this a spell he cast.

609
00:42:27.545 --> 00:42:28.845
some sort of mind control?

610
00:42:28.847 --> 00:42:30.280
I don't know.

611
00:42:30.282 --> 00:42:32.548
I've done everything I can
to reverse the spell.

612
00:42:32.550 --> 00:42:35.284
I can't reach her! It's like
she's on some kind of a loop.

613
00:42:35.286 --> 00:42:39.355
The key to our gate.
into the great undoing.

614
00:42:39.357 --> 00:42:40.556
Four-six...

615
00:42:40.558 --> 00:42:42.291
Where is the gate?

616
00:42:42.293 --> 00:42:44.226
Tell me where they took her!

617
00:42:44.228 --> 00:42:46.028
- Hey! Hey!
- No. no. no. don't.

618
00:42:46.030 --> 00:42:48.664
don't shake her. it may
intensify the spell.

619
00:42:48.666 --> 00:42:50.099
Just try and calm her.

620
00:42:50.101 --> 00:42:51.833
just give her some space.

621
00:42:51.835 --> 00:42:53.235
The way we follow.

622
00:42:53.237 --> 00:42:54.703
the truth we follow.

623
00:42:54.705 --> 00:42:56.405
the light we follow to the gate.

624
00:42:56.407 --> 00:43:00.075
The key that unlocks us
into the great undoing.

625
00:43:00.077 --> 00:43:02.677
Four-six... four-six...

626
00:43:05.215 --> 00:43:08.383
- No. no. no!
- Ah! - No! No. no!

627
00:43:10.353 --> 00:43:11.987
Six...

628
00:43:11.989 --> 00:43:14.455
Aw. no. no. no. no. she's
going to bleed out.

629
00:43:24.600 --> 00:43:25.933
She's gone.

630
00:43:32.474 --> 00:43:33.707
The minute Paige is finished.

631
00:43:33.709 --> 00:43:36.044
you get her to contact Savannah.

632
00:43:36.046 --> 00:43:37.611
You find out if Elena's there

633
00:43:37.613 --> 00:43:40.180
and what is happening to her.

634
00:43:40.182 --> 00:43:41.815
If we don't get her back

635
00:43:41.817 --> 00:43:44.351
you'll have more to worry about
than your missing witch.

636
